VI  - 199
IP  - 4330
DP  - 1978 Feb 17
TI  - Human breast cancer: androgen action mediated by estrogen receptor.
PG  - 787-8
AB  - Growth of the human breast cancer cell line MCF-7 is enhanced by androgens, but 
      only at pharmacological concentrations. Although physiological concentrations of 
      androgens translocate the androgen receptor into the nucleus, no mitogenic 
      effects are observed. By contrast, pharmacological androgens translocate not only 
      the androgen receptor but also the estrogen receptor, and at these high doses 
      significantly increase both DNA and estrogen-dependent protein synthesis. We 
      therefore propose that androgens stimulate MCF-7 cell growth not through the 
      androgen receptor but rather through the estrogen receptor.
