PMID- 282233
OWN - NLM
STAT- MEDLINE
DCOM- 19790328
LR  - 20140724
IP  - 20
DP  - 1978
TI  - HLA frequencies in cancer: a third study.
PG  - 263-9
AB  - Frequencies of 25 HLA antigens in 526 Caucasian patients were compared to those 
      in 629 healthy controls who were HLA-typed between September 1975 and February 
      1977. Haplotypes were compared for 711 patients and 549 controls typed between 
      September 1974 and December 1976. Frequency deviations were found in those with 
      ALL, AML, breast cancer, lymphoma and ovarian cancer, but only the increase in 
      A29 in AML patients was statistically significant when corrected for the number 
      of specificities. Interesting associations, when compared with earlier studies, 
      include elevation of AW24 in both ALL and AML patients and increased B27 in ALL 
      patients. Significant haplotype differences were increased A3-B8 and absence of 
      A1-BW17 in ALL patients and increased A11-B5 and A2-BW40 as well as absence of 
      A2-B5 in AML patients.
