TI  - Banding analysis of three primary cancers.
PG  - 538-41
AB  - Chromosomes of a breast cancer and two colonic cancers were studied with banding 
      methods. An intracystic papillary carcinoma of breast had the following 
      constitution: 46, XX, -1, +3, -20, +i(1q), +i(1q), +t(1;20)(p13;p13). The second 
      tumor, a well-differentiated adenocarcinoma of the colon had several autosomal 
      trisomies and del(3)(p14). There was karyotype stability in both tumors. The 
      third tumor, an undifferentiated colonic cancer, had a pseudodiploid stemline, 
      namely 46, XX, -1, +(1q), and four sidelines with additional numerical changes.
