VI  - 108
IP  - 51
DP  - 1978 Dec 23
TI  - [Biology of breast cancer: current approaches to new treatment modalities].
PG  - 2050-9 concl
AB  - After years of progress, there appear to be few new developments in the treatment 
      of breast cancer at the present time. Aspects of breast cancer are discussed 
      which might offer new therapeutic possibilities. The rather schematic management 
      of the patient with breast cancer is less than well matched with the variable 
      biology and the multitude of factors influencing risk and prognosis. 
      Epidemiological, hereditary, and environmental, as well as endocrinological, 
      immunological, and psychoneurological variables are believed to determine the 
      spontaneous course of the disease and the therapeutic results. One way of 
      improving treatment results is better evaluation of such biological factors in a 
      given patient and variation of treatment plans according to individual needs.
